 The hotly contested by-elections in Mhluzi, Extension 8, came as a result of Cllr Michael Mbatiwe’s passing in July. MEC Mahlangu, Mayor Tolo, ANC candidate Patrick Malinga and other delegates inspected homes of residents and listened to their complaints. Philemon Lukhele, Judith Ngema, Mayor Tsietsi Tolo and MEC Norah Mahlangu. The officials during their house inspection in Ext. 8. Residents have voiced their concerns about the vandalism of RDP houses that has become a safe haven for nyaope boys. ANC members were not the only ones lobbying in the blazing sun on Monday. The EFF was also seen canvassing the area. The DA was nowhere to be seen. Special voting will take place at allocated voting stations on 3rd October between 08:00 and 17:00. The elderly and disabled who have applied for home visits, will be assisted to vote on the 2nd of October. The voting stations are at the Seven Mountains of God tent as well as the Kutana Centre.  R10 000 reward for information ‘We should kill him’ – Truck driver hears how hijackers argue about his fate #TrafficUpdate: Avoid N4 near Machadodorp VIDEO: Machadodorp two granted bail  • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za